Adding brief details on 2 other ways to install 

This package is exactly what I was looking for.  Thanks for creating it.  I found it via conda, so was suprised to see it was not mentioned as an install option (nor homebrew- i tested brew aha on Catalina, it worked, and I tested conda aha on Ubuntu 18 and 20 and it worked).  These routes will certainly make the tool more approachable.  Thanks again--

commit.message: Escape HTML entities when printing stylesheet link (argument to -c / --css)
Escape HTML entities when printing the document language attribute (argument to --lang)
Escape HTML entities when printing bodystyle (argument to -y / --style)
Use "install -D" when installing files to auto-create directories
Will testcases to the repository
Use the INSTALL variable during "make install" and preserve timestamps by default
New version 0.5.1
Updated and synchronized internal and man page help
Added new --style / -y option to man page
Changed short comman of --style from -o to -y

Add --style option

This closes #72

Signed-off-by: Ted Lyngmo <ted@lyncon.se>
Put recent added command line parameters (-c, -r) to man page
Adding option for ignoring carriage-return for solving issue #71
Added css inline option as suggested by issue #68

Merge branch 'polluks-master'

Fix handling of SGR 39/49

SGR 39/49 reset the color back to the default foreground and background
color respectively.

Added vbcc support.
This compiler does not use -std=c99 flag.
